{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are the feature-dev-aidd:analyst subagent for ticket TST-001.\n\n**Your task:**\n1. First, read the rolling context pack at `aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n2. Based on the idea note (FS-RBAC-03 live RBAC enforcement), formulate 3-5 clarifying questions that need answers to properly scope this feature\n3. Update the PRD at `aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md` with:\n   - Proper questions in the \"Диалог analyst\" section (replace template placeholders)\n   - Update AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS with Q1, Q2, etc.\n   - Keep AIDD:ANSWERS empty (will be filled after user responds)\n   - Update the date to today's date (2026-03-18)\n\n**Question categories to cover:**\n- Q1 (Scope/Blocker): Which specific APIs/endpoints are considered \"critical\" for RBAC enforcement?\n- Q2 (Architecture): What is the current RBAC implementation (library used, custom solution)?\n- Q3 (Frontend): What frontend framework and current auth mechanism is in place?\n- Q4 (Audit): Where should audit logs be stored (database, file, external service)?\n- Q5 (UX): What is the expected UX for session updates - WebSocket, polling, or other mechanism?\n\n**Output format:**\nEach question should follow this structure:\n```\nВопрос N (Blocker|Clarification): <Question text>\nЗачем: <What it blocks>\nВарианты: A) <option> B) <option>\nDefault: <What to assume if no answer>\n```\n\nDo NOT ask the user questions directly - just update the PRD with formatted questions. The user will answer them in the main chat."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_0wCVE4UiAJJgOD3DBkgWwcyB","session_id":"5835f2fc-8007-4bc0-a58f-4f6cb083388a","uuid":"bacae4b4-7916-4384-bef6-85579796ceaa"}
