{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_grz62IEdX3IplDz54rXspsxE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# TST-001 Context Pack\n     2→\n     3→## Ticket\n     4→TST-001\n     5→\n     6→## Slug\n     7→fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n     8→\n     9→## Idea Note\n    10→Implement FS-RBAC-03: enforce live RBAC across critical APIs and flow controls, add auditable role operations/403 trail, and synchronize frontend role guards with no-refresh session updates.\n    11→\n    12→## Source Artifacts\n    13→- PRD: `aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n    14→- Status: draft\n    15→\n    16→## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK (Initial)\n    17→- FS-RBAC-03 spec requires live RBAC enforcement on critical API endpoints\n    18→- Need to add audit logging for role operations and 403 responses\n    19→- Frontend role guards must sync with session updates without page refresh\n    20→- Ticket: TST-001\n    21→\n    22→## AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS (Initial)\n    23→- Paths: (to be determined by analyst)\n    24→- Keywords: RBAC, roles, permissions, 403, audit, session, guards\n    25→- Notes: Identify current RBAC implementation, API middleware structure, frontend auth flow\n    26→\n    27→## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n    28→- All critical APIs must enforce RBAC with 403 on violations\n    29→- Role operations must be auditable\n    30→- Frontend must reflect role changes without refresh\n    31→\n    32→## AIDD:GOALS (Draft)\n    33→- Enforce live RBAC across critical APIs\n    34→- Add auditable role operations trail\n    35→- Synchronize frontend role guards with live session updates\n    36→\n    37→## AIDD:RISKS (Draft)\n    38→- Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy\n    39→- Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\n    40→- Audit log storage growth → retention policy\n    41→\n    42→## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE (Draft)\n    43→- AC-1: Critical APIs return 403 for unauthorized role access\n    44→- AC-2: All role operations are logged with timestamp, user, action\n    45→- AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of session change\n    46→\n    47→## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n    48→- Q1: Which APIs are considered \"critical\" and in scope?\n    49→- Q2: What is the current RBAC implementation (library/custom)?\n    50→- Q3: Frontend framework and current auth mechanism?\n    51→- Q4: Audit log storage requirements (DB/file/external)?\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_0wCVE4UiAJJgOD3DBkgWwcyB","session_id":"5835f2fc-8007-4bc0-a58f-4f6cb083388a","uuid":"a699553f-5f3b-4257-b8e6-47f3e1723953"}
